# Party pages live at /councils/party/:slug/* after the /councils
# namespace migration (2026-05-18). The original move from /:slug to
# /party/:slug (2026-05-12) is still honoured because external bookmarks
# from that era exist. Permanent redirects keep both shapes alive.
# Order matters: the catch-all /:slug/:year line below would otherwise
# hijack /:council/:year, so each party slug is listed explicitly.
/labour              /councils/party/labour              301
/labour/*            /councils/party/labour/:splat       301
/conservative        /councils/party/conservative        301
/conservative/*      /councils/party/conservative/:splat 301
/liberal-democrats   /councils/party/liberal-democrats   301
/liberal-democrats/* /councils/party/liberal-democrats/:splat 301
/green               /councils/party/green               301
/green/*             /councils/party/green/:splat        301
/reform              /councils/party/reform              301
/reform/*            /councils/party/reform/:splat       301
/snp                 /councils/party/snp                 301
/snp/*               /councils/party/snp/:splat          301
/plaid-cymru         /councils/party/plaid-cymru         301
/plaid-cymru/*       /councils/party/plaid-cymru/:splat  301
